        {
            "id": "section-2-1772386212848",
            "title": "Structure",
            "type": "formulas",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "type": "code-block",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "",
                    "items": [
                        "Subject + Verb",
                        "I work / He works"
                    ],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "code-block",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "",
                    "items": [
                        "Subject + do/does not (don't/doesn't) + Verb",
                        "I don't work / She doesn't work"
                    ],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "code-block",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "",
                    "items": [
                        "Do/Does + Subject + Verb ?",
                        "Do you work? / Does he work?"
                    ],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "code-block",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "",
                    "items": [
                        "Question Word + do/does + Subject + Verb ?",
                        "Where do they live? / What does he do?"
                    ],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "info-box",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "In affirmative sentences, we add -s, -es, or -ies to the verb ( He, She, It -> 3rd Person Singular)",
                    "items": [],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "info-box",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "In interrogative and negative sentences, we need the auxiliary do (I/You/We/ They) or does (He/She/It)",
                    "items": [],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                },
                {
                    "type": "info-box",
                    "label": "",
                    "content": "In negative and interrogative sentences, the verb stays in its base form (infinitive) because \"does\" already carries the third-person marker.",
                    "items": [],
                    "headers": [],
                    "rows": [],
                    "style": "",
                    "value": "",
                    "description": ""
                }
            ]
        },
